By coincidence, there's another MSc just offered at Bournemouth...

I know nothing about the prestige of Bournemouth.  I only mention it 
because we were just talking about this topic.

--

MSc Applied Artificial Intelligence
MSc Advanced Computing by Research

School of Design, Engineering and Computing, Bournemouth University, UK

Masters degree in Applied Artificial Intelligence with part-time and
full-time options. The course comprises eight taught units and a
Masters dissertation. Topics include:

- Machine Learning
- Evolutionary Computation
- Artificial Neural Networks
- Knowledge Based Systems
- Hybrid Intelligent Systems

Research oriented students may alternatively wish to undertake the
Advanced Computing by Research programme, which offers a combination of
four taught units and an extended research project.

For further information:
http://dec.bournemouth.ac.uk/courses/masters.html
